pageContext.claim: “But when we have this border, it makes it very, very tough for them to come into the United States with women and with children stuffed in trunks in the back of a car.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump doesn't seem to know how human trafficking works in practice. Justice Department news releases announcing convictions of sex traffickers often note how they thwarted checks at legal points of entry, such as obtaining fraudulent visas and travel documents by funding false bank accounts and creating fictitious backgrounds and occupations.
